            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "jYFr6",
              "name": "prose1",
              "fill": "$text-secondary",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": 720,
              "content": "In the landscape of modern systems programming, the intersection of concurrency and predictability remains a significant challenge. As we transition our core services to a more modular architecture, the choice of a state management pattern dictates not just the speed of development, but the long-term reliability of the system.",
              "lineHeight": 1.8,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 16
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "Ax2wn",
              "name": "heading2",
              "fill": "$text-primary",
              "content": "The Core Architecture",
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 28,
              "fontWeight": "700",
              "letterSpacing": -0.5
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "MC4r8",
              "name": "prose2",
              "fill": "$text-secondary",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": 720,
              "content": "Our implementation relies on a directed acyclic graph (DAG) where nodes represent discrete states and edges represent valid transitions governed by strict ownership rules. This approach minimizes the potential for race conditions.",
              "lineHeight": 1.8,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 16
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "5Sgmm",
